<br>
This may seem harsh but it is necessary to ensure everyone has the most enjoyable, hassle-free experience they can.<br>
<br>
Actions that are deemed as grounds for removal from the Silver Hawks:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1. Begging</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
From a Hawk, or anyone. This does not mean that you cannot ask politely for help. Asking repeatedly for anything is deemed as begging. Basically, the first time is asking, then second and subsequent times are considered begging. The person you are asking will help you if they can or want to the first time. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 2. Kill Stealing</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Whether provoked or not, this is unacceptable. If you have any questions about Kill Stealing, read Verants policy. Basically, all Mobs are fair game, (no one owns a spawn). If the mob is green to you, or someone has engaged the creature already and you take the kill, that is a Kill Steal.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 3. Swearing in public channels</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Anyone saying Sh*t, or F**k, or other words known to be even more vulgar in these channels is unacceptable. OOC, Guild, Say, Shout, Auction. If you are grouped with someone that is offended by your language, and your reported, then that is grounds for removal as well. No exceptions. Basically, make sure you know who your cursing to before you do it.<br>
<br>
Also keep in mind you are playing with people from every possible race, creed, color, ethnic, and personal background.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 4. Harassment of another player</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
